The paper deals with the problem of counting triangles in graph streams, which is a fundamental problem in graph algorithms and data structures. The paper presents improved results on this problem, which suggests that it is likely to be submitted to a sub-category related to data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) to analyze the space complexity of the algorithms. Finally, the problem of counting triangles in graph streams is relevant to the field of streaming algorithms (cs.SI), which further supports the inclusion of this paper in this sub-category.
